    • Method Detail

      • getConstValue

        public boolean getConstValue()
        The Classfile Format Spec does not tell how to map a CONSTANT_Integer structure to a boolean value. This method assumes that 0 is false and anything else is true, like in C. Another possibility would be that the presence of a CONSTANT_Integer is true and its absence is false, but that is not the current implementation.
        Specified by:
        getConstValue in interface BooleanConstantElementValue
        Returns:
        false if the matching constant pool entry has value 0, true otherwise.
